OL,3,CMoment of 'astonishing strength' as
OL,4,Cwoman addresses her mother's killer
OL,6,FProsecutor Joanne Martin KC set out
OL,7,Fthe story of the case. Claire Chick
OL,8,Fand Butler first met as neighbours,
OL,9,Fbefore marrying and living together.
OL,10,FThen came Butler's increasingly
OL,11,Ferratic and frightening behaviour.
OL,13,FWe heard that Claire had given six
OL,14,Fstatements to the police in the four
OL,15,Fmonths before her death, Butler had
OL,16,Fbeen arrested several times for
OL,17,Fstalking and repeatedly released on
OL,18,Fbail, and that she had confided in
OL,19,Ffriends and family that she was
OL,20,Fseriously worried he may harm her.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/9
