OL,3,CMoment of 'astonishing strength' as
OL,4,Cwoman addresses her mother's killer
OL,6,FThen came the victim impact
OL,7,Fstatements. Claire's daughters,
OL,8,FBethany and Lydia, stepped forward to
OL,9,Fthe witness box and turned to address
OL,10,Ftheir former stepfather.
OL,12,FThey spoke of unbearable pain, of
OL,13,Fhaving to hide the truth from Claire's
OL,14,Fgrandchildren, some of whom are still
OL,15,Fnot aware of how their beloved 'Ba-ba'
OL,16,Flost her life.
OL,18,F"One day, I am going to have to either
OL,19,Ftell my two children how she died - or
OL,20,Fthey will be told," Bethany said.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/9
