OL,3,CMoment of 'astonishing strength' as
OL,4,Cwoman addresses her mother's killer
OL,6,F"It will likely impact their future
OL,7,Frelationships. If that's what a
OL,8,Fhusband can do, who can they trust?
OL,10,F"I live every day anxious, angry,
OL,11,Fupset, betrayed and feeling completely
OL,12,Flost. I live every day not as Bethany.
OL,13,FI am now the girl whose mother was
OL,14,Fmurdered by her husband."
OL,16,FAddressing Butler directly, Bethany
OL,17,Fsaid: "I have such strong resentment
OL,18,Fof you, the vile evil murderer you
OL,19,Fare."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/9
