OL,3,CMoment of 'astonishing strength' as
OL,4,Cwoman addresses her mother's killer
OL,6,FShe ended by telling him: "I will
OL,7,Fcarry on for my children's sake. I
OL,8,Fwill make sure my mum's legacy lives
OL,9,Fon and I will do everything in my
OL,10,Fpower to make sure that no other women
OL,11,Fwill be betrayed by a monster like
OL,12,Fyou."
OL,14,FIt was a show of astonishing strength
OL,15,Fand human spirit.
OL,17,FMinutes later, Claire's partner Paul
OL,18,FMaxwell gave his own account. Every so
OL,19,Foften he would pause and turn towards
OL,20,FButler in the dock, almost daring the
OL,21,Fmurderer to look him in the eye.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/9
